#. <section class="sutta" id="an5.33"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an5.33:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 5"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.33:0.2"
msgid "4. Sumanavagga"
msgstr "4. With Sumanā"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an5.33:0.3"
msgid "33. Uggahasutta"
msgstr "33. With Uggaha"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an5.33:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā bhaddiye viharati jātiyā vane."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Bhaddiya, in Jātiyā Wood."

msgctxt "an5.33:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho uggaho meṇḍakanattā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā "
"bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho uggaho "
"meṇḍakanattā bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then Uggaha, Meṇḍaka’s grandson, went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to "
"one side, and said to him:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.37"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an5.33:2.1"
msgid "“Adhivāsetu me, bhante, bhagavā svātanāya attacatuttho bhattan”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Sir, may the Buddha please accept tomorrow’s meal from me, together with "
"three other monks.”"

msgctxt "an5.33:2.2"
msgid "Adhivāsesi bhagavā tuṇhībhāvena."
msgstr "The Buddha consented in silence."

msgctxt "an5.33:2.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho uggaho meṇḍakanattā bhagavato adhivāsanaṃ viditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā "
"bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkāmi."
msgstr ""
"Then, knowing that the Buddha had accepted, Uggaha got up from his seat, "
"bowed, and respectfully circled the Buddha, keeping him on his right, before "
"leaving."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an5.33:3.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā tassā rattiyā accayena pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā "
"pattacīvaramādāya yena uggahassa meṇḍakanattuno nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami; "
"upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi."
msgstr ""
"Then when the night had passed, the Buddha robed up in the morning and, "
"taking his bowl and robe, went to Uggaha’s home, where he sat on the seat "
"spread out."

msgctxt "an5.33:3.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho uggaho meṇḍakanattā bhagavantaṃ paṇītena khādanīyena bhojanīyena "
"sahatthā santappesi sampavāresi."
msgstr ""
"Then Uggaha served and satisfied the Buddha with his own hands with a "
"variety of delicious foods."

msgctxt "an5.33:3.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho uggaho meṇḍakanattā bhagavantaṃ bhuttāviṃ onītapattapāṇiṃ ekamantaṃ "
"nisīdi."
msgstr ""
"When the Buddha had eaten and washed his hand and bowl, Uggaha sat down to "
"one side,"

msgctxt "an5.33:3.4"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho uggaho meṇḍakanattā bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "and said to him:"

msgctxt "an5.33:3.5"
msgid "“imā me, bhante, kumāriyo patikulāni gamissanti."
msgstr "“Sir, these girls of mine will be going to their husbands’ families."

msgctxt "an5.33:3.6"
msgid "Ovadatu tāsaṃ, bhante, bhagavā;"
msgstr "May the Buddha please advise"

msgctxt "an5.33:3.7"
msgid ""
"anusāsatu tāsaṃ, bhante, bhagavā, yaṃ tāsaṃ assa dīgharattaṃ hitāya "
"sukhāyā”ti."
msgstr "and instruct them. It will be for their lasting welfare and happiness.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an5.33:4.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā tā kumāriyo etadavoca:"
msgstr "Then the Buddha said to those girls:"

msgctxt "an5.33:4.2"
msgid "“tasmātiha, kumāriyo, evaṃ sikkhitabbaṃ:"
msgstr "“So, girls, you should train like this:"

#. VAR: yassa vo → yassa kho (si, s1-3, km) | yassa (pts1)
msgctxt "an5.33:4.3"
msgid ""
"‘yassa vo mātāpitaro bhattuno dassanti atthakāmā hitesino anukampakā "
"anukampaṃ upādāya, tassa bhavissāma pubbuṭṭhāyiniyo pacchānipātiniyo "
"kiṃkārapaṭissāviniyo manāpacāriniyo piyavādiniyo’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Our parents will give us to a husband wanting what’s best, out of kindness "
"and compassion. We will get up before him and go to bed after him, and be "
"obliging, behaving nicely and speaking politely.’"

msgctxt "an5.33:4.4"
msgid "Evañhi vo, kumāriyo, sikkhitabbaṃ."
msgstr "That’s how you should train."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an5.33:5.1"
msgid "Tasmātiha, kumāriyo, evaṃ sikkhitabbaṃ:"
msgstr "So, girls, you should train like this:"

#. VAR: garuno → guruno (mr)
#. VAR: garuṃ karissāma → garukarissāma (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
#. VAR: paṭipūjessāmā’ti → patipūjessāmāti (bj) | paṭipūjissāmāti (pts1)
msgctxt "an5.33:5.2"
msgid ""
"‘ye te bhattu garuno bhavissanti mātāti vā pitāti vā samaṇabrāhmaṇāti vā, te "
"sakkarissāma garuṃ karissāma mānessāma pūjessāma abbhāgate ca āsanodakena "
"paṭipūjessāmā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Those our husband respects—mother and father, ascetics and brahmins—we will "
"honor, respect, revere, and venerate, and serve with a seat and a drink when "
"they come as guests.’"

msgctxt "an5.33:5.3"
msgid "Evañhi vo, kumāriyo, sikkhitabbaṃ."
msgstr "That’s how you should train."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an5.33:6.1"
msgid "Tasmātiha, kumāriyo, evaṃ sikkhitabbaṃ:"
msgstr "So, girls, you should train like this:"

msgctxt "an5.33:6.2"
msgid ""
"‘ye te bhattu abbhantarā kammantā uṇṇāti vā kappāsāti vā, tattha dakkhā "
"bhavissāma analasā, tatrupāyāya vīmaṃsāya samannāgatā, alaṃ kātuṃ alaṃ "
"saṃvidhātun’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘We will be skilled and tireless in doing domestic duties for our husband, "
"such as knitting and sewing. We will have an understanding of how to go "
"about things in order to complete and organize the work.’"

msgctxt "an5.33:6.3"
msgid "Evañhi vo, kumāriyo, sikkhitabbaṃ."
msgstr "That’s how you should train."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.38"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an5.33:7.1"
msgid "Tasmātiha, kumāriyo, evaṃ sikkhitabbaṃ:"
msgstr "So, girls, you should train like this:"

#. VAR: abbhantaro → abbhantare (mr)
#. VAR: paccaṃsena → paccayaṃsena (si, s1-3, km) | paccayaṃ senāsanaṃ paccattaṃsena (mr)
#. VAR: saṃvibhajissāmā’ti → vibhajissāmāti (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an5.33:7.2"
msgid ""
"‘yo so bhattu abbhantaro antojano dāsāti vā pessāti vā kammakarāti vā, tesaṃ "
"katañca katato jānissāma akatañca akatato jānissāma, gilānakānañca balābalaṃ "
"jānissāma, khādanīyaṃ bhojanīyañcassa paccaṃsena saṃvibhajissāmā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘We will know what work our husband’s domestic bondservants, workers, and "
"staff have completed, and what they’ve left incomplete. We will know who is "
"sick, and who is fit or unwell. We will distribute to each a fair portion of "
"various foods.’"

msgctxt "an5.33:7.3"
msgid "Evañhi vo, kumāriyo, sikkhitabbaṃ."
msgstr "That’s how you should train."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an5.33:8.1"
msgid "Tasmātiha, kumāriyo, evaṃ sikkhitabbaṃ:"
msgstr "So, girls, you should train like this:"

#. VAR: ārakkhena → ārakkhāya (si)
msgctxt "an5.33:8.2"
msgid ""
"‘yaṃ bhattā āharissati dhanaṃ vā dhaññaṃ vā rajataṃ vā jātarūpaṃ vā, taṃ "
"ārakkhena guttiyā sampādessāma, tattha ca bhavissāma adhuttī athenī asoṇḍī "
"avināsikāyo’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘We will ensure that any income our husbands earn is guarded and protected, "
"whether money, grain, silver, or gold. We will not overspend, steal, waste, "
"or lose it.’"

msgctxt "an5.33:8.3"
msgid "Evañhi vo, kumāriyo, sikkhitabbaṃ."
msgstr "That’s how you should train."

msgctxt "an5.33:8.4"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho, kumāriyo, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato mātugāmo kāyassa bhedā "
"paraṃ maraṇā manāpakāyikānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjatīti."
msgstr ""
"When they have these five qualities, females—when their body breaks up, "
"after death—are reborn in company with the Gods of the Loveable Group."

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "an5.33:9.1"
msgid "Yo naṃ bharati sabbadā,"
msgstr "She’d never look down on her husband,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.33:9.2"
msgid "niccaṃ ātāpi ussuko;"
msgstr "who’s always keen to work hard,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.33:9.3"
msgid "Sabbakāmaharaṃ posaṃ,"
msgstr "always looking after her,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.33:9.4"
msgid "bhattāraṃ nātimaññati."
msgstr "and bringing whatever she wants."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "an5.33:10.1"
msgid "Na cāpi sotthi bhattāraṃ,"
msgstr "And a good woman never scolds her husband"

#. <br>
#. VAR: issācārena → icchācārena (bj) | issāvādena (pts1)
msgctxt "an5.33:10.2"
msgid "issācārena rosaye;"
msgstr "with jealous words."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.33:10.3"
msgid "Bhattu ca garuno sabbe,"
msgstr "Being astute, she reveres"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.33:10.4"
msgid "paṭipūjeti paṇḍitā."
msgstr "those respected by her husband."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
#. VAR: Uṭṭhāhikā → uṭṭhāyikā (s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "an5.33:11.1"
msgid "Uṭṭhāhikā analasā,"
msgstr "She gets up early, works tirelessly,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.33:11.2"
msgid "saṅgahitaparijjanā;"
msgstr "and manages the domestic help."

#. <br>
#. VAR: manāpaṃ → manāpā (bj)
msgctxt "an5.33:11.3"
msgid "Bhattu manāpaṃ carati,"
msgstr "She’s loveable to her husband,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.33:11.4"
msgid "sambhataṃ anurakkhati."
msgstr "and preserves his wealth."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "an5.33:12.1"
msgid "Yā evaṃ vattatī nārī,"
msgstr "A lady who fulfills these duties"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.33:12.2"
msgid "bhattuchandavasānugā;"
msgstr "according to her husbands desire,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.33:12.3"
msgid "Manāpā nāma te devā,"
msgstr "is reborn among the gods"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.33:12.4"
msgid "yattha sā upapajjatī”ti."
msgstr "called ‘Loveable’.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.33:12.5"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
